					<description><![CDATA[<p>Skello Raises €200 Million to Accelerate European Growth Skello, an AI-powered platform helping businesses manage their front-line workers, has secured a $200 million investment from the firm, led by Bridgepoint,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/skello-raises-200-million-european-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Skello Raises €200M to Expand AI Workforce Management Across Europe</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Skello Raises €200 Million to Accelerate European Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Skello, an AI-powered platform helping businesses manage their front-line workers, has secured a $200 million investment from the firm, led by Bridgepoint, in a bid to accelerate growth across Europe. The company hit profitability in 2025 and topped $50 million in annual recurring revenue in 2026.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Current investors, Partech and XAnge, took part by reinvesting alongside the founder and management team, in the company which offers scheduling, payroll, compliance, and planning software to employers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Skello, headquartered in Paris, stated that the new funds will drive future product development, boost its geographic reach and enable selective acquisitions. Skello’s founders and management have boosted their stake in the firm, atypical of many rounds of this size, amid strong financial results. </span></p>
<h2><b>AI Platform Supports Frontline Workforce Management<br />
</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The software platform of Skello for front-end employees, who make up the majority of workers in Europe’s workforce. Many businesses continue to create shift rotas via manual methods, or using outdated Excel spreadsheets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Skello’s software helps managers to design shifts around forecasts like revenues, historical data, and available resources. On the other side, workers are able to view the rota, ask for shifts to be </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/swapped" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">swapped</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and clock their time via a mobile application.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Last year, the company announced it was building out AI for a Skello Assistant that can identify patterns and discrepancies from scheduling and payroll, flag up overtime, and provide suggestions for managing the schedule, before operations even encounter problems. </span></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Plans Include Hiring and Acquisitions<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203363" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203363" class="size-full wp-image-203363" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-depicts-a-s_nCJQ3dIIWHi_BxyrQviLnQ_EA-PpXp_Tdu0_gdovOH3bA-1.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI-driven workforce management and business expansion across Europe." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203363" class="wp-caption-text">Skello accelerates European expansion and AI development as it scales workforce management across a fragmented market. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Skello will utilize the capital to both solidify its foothold in France and accelerate expansion throughout Europe. In parallel, the software will enhance its features via further AI development and strategic takeovers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Having begun operations in 2016 under co-founders Quitterie Mathelin-Moreaux and Emmanuelle Fauchier-Magnan, Skello currently caters to over 30,000 companies across the countries of Spain, Italy, Benelux, and its native France, anticipating 100 hires in 2026.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Engineering, product development and sales are areas where hires are likely, in Paris, Lille and Barcelona. Acquiring further, smaller competitors, according to the company, is a key element of consolidation within Europe’s fractured workforce management market. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company states it’s not raising capital to fuel everyday operations, rather to fortify its position, operating from a position of profit. Co-founders said the investment supports European expansion, AI investment, and long-term consolidation plans.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/keyfactor-raises-1-billion-strategic-investment/" data-wpel-link="internal">Keyfactor Raises $1B+ Strategic Investment to Expand Trust Infrastructure</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Fragmented HR Software Market Creates Opportunity</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Demand for digital workforce management tools is booming with companies looking to modernize their frontline operations. These customers want tools that integrate scheduling, compliance, payroll, and workforce analytics in a one-stop-shop, and that&#8217;s where Skello&#8217;s offering comes into play. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridgepoint sees the European market as &#8220;highly fragmented,&#8221; offering a lot of scope for established companies to grow organically and by acquisition. Jean-Baptiste Salvin commented on Skello&#8217;s leadership in its market, noting that it is a &#8220;fast-growing and well-differentiated business.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding is also an indication of optimism in the applications of AI targeted at operational teams rather than office staff, and more broadly shows a move towards companies implementing software for an efficient and compliant workforce as regulatory complexity rises. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Armed with the new investment, proven profitability and a client base of over 700,000 daily users, Skello is working towards becoming a dominant force in the European frontline workforce management market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
