					<description><![CDATA[<p>Keyfactor Raises $1 Billion to Accelerate AI Security Platform Keyfactor nets over $1 billion in strategic growth investment to bolster platform for age of AI and quantum computing Keyfactor has</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/keyfactor-raises-1-billion-strategic-investment/" data-wpel-link="internal">Keyfactor Raises $1B+ Strategic Investment to Expand Trust Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Keyfactor Raises $1 Billion to Accelerate AI Security Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Keyfactor nets over $1 billion in strategic growth investment to bolster platform for age of AI and quantum computing Keyfactor has secured over $1 billion in strategic growth investment led by Summit Partners. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round also includes significant participation from earlier investors Insight Partners and Sixth Street Growth, who will retain a meaningful minority ownership interest. The investment round will be invested in product innovation, international expansion, workforce augmentation and strategic acquisitions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This infusion of capital occurs as large enterprises ramp up investment in machine identity management and quantum security preparation, two burgeoning enterprise areas of interest. Keyfactor develops a single platform managing all of a business’s digital certificates and other cryptographic credentials.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to Jordan Rackie, “Keyfactor’s approach was validation. With this capital, we will significantly accelerate growth and expand Keyfactor globally to support the urgent need for identity for the coming era of AI and quantum.”</span></p>
<h2><b>Rising Security Risks Increase Demand for Trust Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As businesses adopt a more connected ecosystem of cloud, IoT devices, and AI, the number of machine identities has proliferated. Machine identities outnumber human identities in a lot of organizations, creating additional cybersecurity problems to contend with. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fragmented security systems cannot continue to scale with the increase in machine identities, Keyfactor said. Its Trust Control Plane centralises visibility across certificates, cryptographic assets and digital trust systems while automating lifecycle management and governance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also expects demand to increase as governments prepare for post-quantum cryptography. Recent policy initiatives encourage organisations to begin replacing current encryption methods before quantum computing makes existing standards vulnerable.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Summit Partners Managing Director Andy Collins said several trends are driving greater urgency across enterprise security. These include shrinking certificate lifespans, tighter regulations, AI governance requirements and the transition towards quantum-safe cryptography.</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Customer Growth Supports Expansion<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203359" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203359" class="size-full wp-image-203359" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-complex-_rJSYgIqcWMi6xO7SV_oAYg_xvACcqFhQMyH3MODLdmgGg.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing global enterprise systems secured by machine identity management and automated cybersecurity infrastructure." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203359" class="wp-caption-text">Keyfactor expands globally as enterprise demand for machine identity management and compliance-ready security infrastructure continues to grow. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Keyfactor enters its next growth phase from a position of financial strength. It added it was accelerating annual revenue growth and remained profitable at billions of machine identities per year for its over 2,500 customers across 150 countries. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These customers include half of the biggest banks in the U.S and Europe, 80% of U.S. Biggest retailers, and 40% of Fortune 100 organizations. In terms of vertical adoption, Keyfactor said its solution is widely used within financial services, healthcare, technology, telecommunications and government.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlier this year, the company achieved FedRAMP certification. The milestone enables federal agencies and public sector organisations to adopt its cloud-based certificate lifecycle automation platform while meeting government security requirements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Summit Partners Managing Director Colin Mistele said growing preparation for post-quantum compliance creates a significant long-term opportunity for the business. He believes Keyfactor&#8217;s relationships with financial institutions and governments position it for international growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/twelvelabs-raises-100m-series-b-to-advance-video-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">TwelveLabs Raises $100M Series B to Advance Video Intelligence</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investment Reflects Expanding Cybersecurity Market</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment highlights increasing interest in </span><a href="https://www.cisco.com/site/us/en/learn/topics/security/what-is-cybersecurity.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">cybersecurity</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> companies supporting artificial intelligence infrastructure. As enterprises adopt AI systems, connected devices and automated workloads, the need to secure digital identities continues to grow.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Keyfactor provides an integrated platform covering certificate discovery, issuance, and ongoing lifecycle management.</span> <span style="font-weight: 400">The company argues this approach simplifies security operations while improving resilience across complex enterprise environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment also strengthens Summit Partners&#8217; exposure to enterprise infrastructure software. Following completion of the transaction, Andy Collins and Colin Mistele will join Keyfactor&#8217;s board of directors to support its next phase of expansion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
